==English==

===Etymology===
Relating to the [[shyness]] of [[bairns]] ([[children]]) for making [[requests]].

===Alternative spellings===
*[[shy bairns get noot]]

===Phrase===
'''[[shy]] [[bairns]] [[get]] [[nowt]]'''

# {{cattag|Geordie|idiom}} If you're too [[shy]], or don't ask, you will not get what you want.
#: ''"A' forgot te ask hor for me money back!"
#: ''"Wye, [[shy bairns get nowt]]"''

===Usage notes===
*Use widely in the North East of [[England]] and is often used to [[encourage]] [[children]] to speak up and not to be too [[shy]].
*Used also by adults to imply others are too [[shy]].
*Used to say that you should never be afraid to ask, because if you ask there's a chance might get what you want, if you don't ask, you'll never get it. 

